@ilooner, could you please remove other places in tests where results are printed using `System.out.println()`. For example, in `TestHiveUDFs`, `ExpressionTest`, `TestPartitionSender`, `TestSimpleProjection`, `TestConvertFunctions`, `TestFragmentChecker`, `JdbcTestActionBase`, `ITTestShadedJar` it also may be removed; for every HBase test its result is printed for now.
Mongo and hive tests have a large output, it would be fine to reduce it.

Also, may be changed value of the option `drill.test.query.printing.silent` to reduce output.

@akumarb2010  I haven't gone through @aravi5 's PR in detail, but I did see an interactive demo where we tried out quite a few of the scenarios. 
Semantically, it might not make much sense define offsets without specifying partitions, but it doesn't hurt to have the capability. We were trying to do  exploration of stream data during the demo, and offsets might prove to be a good way to just explore data in a topic on the assumption that the offsets for all the partitions are not wildly different for a similar time range (that is not granular).
Only if there is a benefit of adding to the complexity of the code, such as performance (or even debugging issues), it  _might_ be worth pursuing the additional changes.

@aravi5  & @kkhatua  

In production environments, most of the scenarios, I observed non uniform offset ranges(cases where repartition etc). But, If handling this scenario needs complex logic, then we can go ahead with current design. 

I just started going through the code, will update my review comments by this weekend, if there is any.
